						<summary>

						<p>The portion of the inscription after line, 13 is completely damaged. It seems to record some gift to the temple of Mahādēva at Tiruviḍaimarudu, made during the administration of <hi rend="bold">Śandirāchchaṉ Śatturugaṇḍaṉ of Varampūśal</hi> in Veṇṇāḍu. Reference is made to <hi rend="italic">Kumaramāt[tāṇḍa]</hi>, probably a liquid measure, called after the surname of Pallava Nandivarman III. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
